# 🚀 Terraform AWS Infrastructure – DevOps Workflow

## 📌 Overview
This project demonstrates a complete DevOps workflow using Terraform to provision and manage AWS infrastructure.

## 🔄 DevOps Workflow

1. Code → Terraform (IaC)
2. Validate → terraform fmt & validate
3. Plan → terraform plan
4. Deploy → terraform apply
5. Output → EC2 IP, VPC ID
6. Destroy → terraform destroy

1. Code
- Infrastructure defined using Terraform (IaC)

2. Validate
- terraform fmt
- terraform validate

3. Plan
- terraform plan (preview infrastructure changes)

4. Deploy
- terraform apply (provision resources)

5. Monitor Output
- Outputs include VPC ID and EC2 Public IP

6. Destroy (Cleanup)
- terraform destroy

## 🏗️ Architecture

- VPC → Network layer
- Subnet → Public access
- EC2 → Compute instance

## ⚙️ Automation

- Shell scripts automate Terraform lifecycle
- CI/CD pipeline using GitHub Actions validates every commit

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
- Terraform
- AWS
- GitHub Actions

## 📊 Infrastructure Created
- VPC
- Subnet
- EC2 Instance

## 🚀 How to Run

```bash
./scripts/init.sh
./scripts/plan.sh
./scripts/apply.sh